The G-Blog

Author: [Gregg Ochieng]
Description

The G-Blog is a simple blogging program built with Sinatra and ActiveRecord, allowing users to create, edit, and delete articles, as well as leave comments on articles.
Project Setup
Prerequisites

    Ruby (version 2.7.4)
    Bundler

Installation

    Clone the repository to your local machine.
    Navigate to the project directory.
    Run bundle install to install dependencies.
    Set up the database by running rake db:create and rake db:migrate.
    Start the server with ruby app.rb.
    Visit http://localhost:4567 in your web browser to view the application.

Live Site

A live version of the application can be found on GitHub Pages at link to "https://the-g-blog.onrender.com".
